                      our Website. Depending on your activities when visiting our Website, you may be required to agree to additional terms and conditions.
                  </p><br />
                  <b>- Website Visitors</b>
                  <p>
                      Like most website operators, Canadian Association for Girls in Science collects non-personally-identifying information of the sort that web<br />
                      browsers and servers typically make available, such as the browser type, language preference, referring site, and the date and time of each visitor<br />
                      request. Canadian Association for Girls in Science’s purpose in collecting non-personally identifying information is to better understand how<br />
                      Canadian Association for Girls in Science’s visitors use its website. From time to time, Canadian Association for Girls in Science may release non-<br />
                      personally-identifying information in the aggregate, e.g., by publishing a report on trends in the usage of its website.<br />
                      Canadian Association for Girls in Science also collects potentially personally-identifying information like Internet Protocol (IP) addresses for logged<br />
                      in users and for users leaving comments on http://GirlsInScience.ca blog posts. Canadian Association for Girls in Science only discloses logged in<br />
                      user and commenter IP addresses under the same circumstances that it uses and discloses personally-identifying information as described below.
                  </p><br />
                  <b>- Gathering of Personally-Indentifying Information</b>
                  <p>
                      Certain visitors to Canadian Association for Girls in Science’s websites choose to interact with Canadian Association for Girls in Science in ways that<br />
                      require Canadian Association for Girls in Science to gather personally-identifying information. The amount and type of information that Canadian<br />
                      Association for Girls in Science gathers depends on the nature of the interaction. For example, we ask visitors who sign up for a newsletter at<br />
                      http://GirlsInScience.ca to provide an email address. Visitors who sign up to volunteer are asked for more information.
                  </p><br />
